% --- Project Euler Problem 17 --- %
\begin{tcbProblem}[label={problem:0017:question:Eng}]
	If the numbers 1 to 5 are written out in words: one, two, three, four, five, then there are \( 3 \mathplus 3 \mathplus 5 \mathplus 4 \mathplus 4 \equal 19 \) letters used in total.

	If all the numbers from 1 to 1000 (one thousand) inclusive were written out in words, how many letters would be used?\\%

	{\small
		\emph{NOTE:}
		Do not count spaces or hyphens.
		For example, 342 (three hundred and forty-two) contains 23 letters and 115 (one hundred and fifteen) contains 20 letters.
		The use of ``and'' when writing out numbers is in compliance with British usage.
	}
	\par%
	\hrefOriginalPage{17}%
	\tcbline%
	1から5までの数字を英単語で書けばone, two, three, four, five であり，
	全部で\( 3 \mathplus 3 \mathplus 5 \mathplus 4 \mathplus 4 \equal 19 \)の文字が使われている.
	では1から1000 (one thousand)までの数字をすべて英単語で書けば，
	全部で何文字になるか．\\%

	{\small
		\emph{注：}
		空白文字やハイフンを数えないこと．
		例えば，342 (three hundred and forty-two)は23文字，
		115 (one hundred and fifteen)は20文字と数える．
		なお，``and''を使用するのは英国の慣習.
	}\par%
	\hrefTransitionPageJpn{17}%
\end{tcbProblem}
